  "text": "T clustered within the genus Syntrophobacter, in the d-subclass of the Proteobacteria, and was most closely related to strain HP1.1 [CITATION_1] (99?2 % similarity), a highly purified propionate-degrading culture, and Syntrophobacter fumaroxidans DSM 10017 T (94?7 % similarity) and Syntrophobacter pfennigii DSM 10092 T (94?6 % similarity).",
